<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I am using 180hz 2560x1440 lg 27GP850. I recently bought it as a new one.</p> <p>It works fine on windows, no flickering but on linux it turns screen black every few minutes for a millisecond. Sometimes it flickers like a 3 times a row and stops for a next few minutes. I saw that It doesn&#39;t happen in full screen games. I am using xwayland gnome but I checked on x11 KDE plasma and it also happens. </p> <p>XRANDR output</p> <p>Screen 0: minimum 16 x 16, current 4000 x 1599, maximum 32767 x 32767</p> <p>XWAYLAND0 connected primary 2560x1440+0+0 (normal left inverted right x axis y axis) 700mm x 390mm</p> <p>2560x1440 179.90*+</p> <p>1920x1440 179.86 </p> <p>[some other resolutions...]</p> <p>inxi -G output </p> <p>Graphics:</p> <p>Device-1: AMD Navi 23 [Radeon RX 6600/6600 XT/6600M] driver: amdgpu</p> <p>v: kernel</p> <p>Display: wayland server: <a href="https://X.org">X.org</a> v: <a href="https://1.21.1.4">1.21.1.4</a> with: Xwayland v: 22.1.3</p> <p>compositor: gnome-shell v: 42.3.1 driver: X: loaded: amdgpu</p> <p>unloaded: modesetting,vesa gpu: amdgpu resolution: 1: 2560x1440~180Hz</p> <p>2: 1440x900~75Hz</p> <p>OpenGL: renderer: AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT (dimgrey_cavefish LLVM 14.0.6</p> <p>DRM 3.46 5.18.13-arch1-1)</p> <p>v: 4.6 Mesa 22.1.3</p> <p>CPU: I5 10400F</p> <p>GPU: RX 6600 XT (bought 3 months ago as a new one)</p> <p>RAM: 16GiB</p> <p>Monitor settings: </p> <p>Overclock: ON (It doesn&#39;t change anything if I turn this off only refresh rate goes from 165 to 180hz)</p> <p>response time: faster (It also doesn&#39;t change anything)</p> <p>Energy saving: OFF</p> <p>HDR: off </p> <p>motion blur reduction: off</p> <p>VRR: ON (in gnome settings)</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/efoxpl3244"> /u/efoxpl3244 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w71ciq/screen_flickering_black_for_a_milisecond_every/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https